<!--
    Icelandic — is
    Script : Latin (+ Icelandic-specific letters: á é í ó ú ý ö ð þ æ); LTR.
             Do NOT strip or replace the special characters — they are
             semantically and orthographically essential in Icelandic.
    Approx.: ~380 000 speakers (Iceland + diaspora).
    Register: Standard written Icelandic (staðlað ritmal).
    Notes  : Icelandic has four grammatical cases and grammatical gender.
             Noun phrases agree in gender, number, and case.  "Binge drinking"
             → óhóflegt drykkjulæti / glápur — the more clinical term
             óhóflegt drykkjulæti is preferred in health contexts.
    Source : Translated from values-de/strings.xml (German source of truth).
-->
